== Description ==

The [[Image:Sketcher_Dimensioning.svg|24px]] [[Sketcher_Dimensioning|Sketcher Dimensioning]] tool is a smart, context-sensitive constraint tool. It automatically detects the selected elements (points, lines, arcs) and applies the most appropriate dimensional constraint (Horizontal, Vertical, Angular, or Diametric/Radiametric).

Additionally, it supports '''Chain Dimensioning''' (continuous serial constraints) which allows drawing multiple sequential dimensions much faster than legacy tools.

== Usage ==

# Ensure you are inside an active edit sketch mode.
# Click the {{Button|[[Image:Sketcher_Dimensioning.svg|16px]] [[Sketcher_Dimensioning|Constrain dimensioning]]}} button or press the {{KEY|D}} key.
# Select the geometric element(s) you want to constrain:
#* Select a single line to apply length or distance.
#* Select two points or a line and a point to set distance.
#* Select two intersecting lines to apply an angle constraint.
#* Select a circle or arc to apply a radius or diameter constraint.
# Right-click or press {{KEY|Esc}} to exit the continuous placement mode.

== Properties ==

This tool utilizes standard FreeCAD constraint properties such as {{PropertyData|Value}} for distance/angle tuning and {{PropertyData|Name}} for identification.

== Versioning ==
* This unified tool was introduced in the major Sketcher refactor for FreeCAD v1.1 to replace repetitive separate clicks.

